{
  "page": "Saan family",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Saan family</b> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lysene</a> line of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_Freehold\" title=\"Valyrian Freehold\">Valyrian</a> descent that has produced a number of famous <a href=\"/index.php/Pirates\" title=\"Pirates\">pirates</a> over the centuries. Saans have been distinguished pirate-lords for at least three hundred years, dating back to the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon the Conqueror</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Saan_family_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\">The Saan family at the end of the third century</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Saan_family&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Saan family at the end of the third century\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Salladhor_Saan\" title=\"Salladhor Saan\">Salladhor Saan</a>, self styled <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_the_Narrow_Sea\" title=\"Prince of the Narrow Sea\">Prince of the Narrow Sea</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pirate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pirate\">pirate</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsail\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsail\">sellsail</a>, smuggler and trader, declared the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Blackwater_Bay\" title=\"Lord of Blackwater Bay\">Lord of Blackwater Bay</a> by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alester_Florent\" title=\"Alester Florent\">Alester Florent</a>. Abandoned his contract to fight for <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> and now in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a> engaging in piracy.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Historical_Saans\">Historical Saans</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Saan_family&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Historical Saans\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Sargoso_Saan\" title=\"Sargoso Saan\">Sargoso Saan</a>, a pirate-lord active in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a> late in the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Saathos_Saan\" title=\"Saathos Saan\">Saathos Saan</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lysene</a> captain who led a fleet to the <a href=\"/index.php/Basilisk_Isles\" title=\"Basilisk Isles\">Basilisk Isles</a> to clear out its pirates, only to turn pirate himself. He became a great pirate-lord, uniting and reigning them as <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Basilisk_Isles\" title=\"King of the Basilisk Isles\">King of the Basilisk Isles</a> for thirty years. He lived at some point after the Basilisk Isles were resettled, which occurred during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Samarro_Saan\" title=\"Samarro Saan\">Samarro Saan</a>, <i>the Last Valyrian</i>, a member of the <a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a>, during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys II Targaryen\">Jaehaerys II Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References_and_Notes\">References and Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Saan_family&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References and Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php/topic/115696-spoilers-sons-of-the-dragon-reading-at-loncon-today/page-15#entry6140859\">Westeros Forum, \"The Sons of the Dragon\", read at LonCon 2014</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Basilisk Isles.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Jaehaerys II.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403194622\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.013 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.015 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 256/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8644/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 741/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 214/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2024/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    8.571      1 -total\n 70.50%    6.042      3 Template:Ref\n 42.48%    3.641      3 Template:Ref/core\n 23.81%    2.041      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:18520-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403194622 and revision id 232637\n -->\n",
